1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new chapter to title 23 and a new section to chapter
2 47-32 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to receivers for mobile home parks and a
3 defense to an eviction from a mobile home; to amend and reenact sections 23-10-03, 23-10-04,
4 23-10-06, 23-10-06.2, 23-10-12, and 47-10-28 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to
5 licensure and regulation of mobile home parks; and to provide a penalty.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
7 SECTION 1. A new chapter to title 23 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
8 enacted as follows:
9 Definitions.
10 For purpose of this chapter:
11 1. "Commissioner" means the commissioner of the department.
12 2. "Department" means the department of health and human services.
13 Conditions for appointment of receiver.
14 1. When the department revokes the license of a mobile home park, the department may
15 file a petition with the district court to place the mobile home park under the control of
16 a receiver for repeated or serious violations of chapter 23 - 10 or the administrative
17 rules of the department, or to protect health or safety.
18 2. The court may grant the petition after finding:
19 a. The mobile home park committed, or is continuing to commit repeated or serious
20 violations of chapter 23 - 10 or the administrative rules of the department; or
21 b. Health or safety would be seriously threatened if a condition existing at the time
22 the petition was filed continues.
